      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Another race decimated by scratchings. VATICAN (5) was no match for the speedy Where's The Circus on debut with a plugging fifth over 1000m in the LR Inglis Nursery at Randwick last December 13. Improved further over the break with the two good trial placings and will prove too good for these. SATOSHI (4) Wootton Bassett colt from My Sabeel on debut for the Price & Kent yard. Sharp trial winner over 736m at Randwick. Impeccably bred colt who looks the only danger. SILVER DREAM (6) well-supported at debut with a plugging fifth over 1000m at Tamworth. Further improved for this and can sneak into the minor money. TWIGGIES (7) unwanted in betting on debut and ran accordingly with a poor tenth over 1000m at Muswellbrook. Unlikely to trouble these and can earn some minor prize money.",
